The paper proposes a novel method for knowledge base completion using hierarchical attention networks and joint adversarial training. This involves encoding inputs into low-dimensional vectors and exploiting two partial parameter-shared components. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the CS sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computation and Language (cs.CL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information retrieval and databases, which are associated with the CS sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Databases (cs.DB).
